any Stamp\n[Stamp Here]', now(), now()),

('15_financial_reconciliation_deal_ledger', 'Financial Reconciliation & Deal Ledger', 'Other', 'v1.0', 'Published', E'Financial Reconciliation & Deal Ledger\n\nPurpose\nThis ledger records all financial movements for a specific deal, enabling reconciliation and audit verification.\n\n1. Deal Information\nDeal Reference: __________________________________________\nProperty Address: _______________________________________\nTransaction Type: [  ] Sale  [  ] Lease\nCompletion Date: ________________________________________\n\n2. Ledger Entries\nDate | Description | Debit (AED) | Credit (AED) | Balance (AED)\n--- | --- | --- | --- | ---\n__________ | __________________________ | ______ | ______ | ______\n__________ | __________________________ | ______ | ______ | ______\n__________ | __________________________ | ______ | ______ | ______\n\n3. Reconciliation Summary\nTotal Receipts (AED): _________________________________\nTotal Payments (AED): _________________________________\nNet Balance (AED): ____________________________________\nReconciled By: ________________________________________\nReconciliation Date: ___________________________________\n\n4. Notes\n__________________________________________________________________\n__________________________________________________________________\n\n5. Governing Law\nThis ledger is maintained in accordance with the laws of the United Arab Emirates and applicable regulations in the Emirate of Abu Dhabi.\n\nSignatures\n\nFinance Officer\nName: __________________________________________\nSignature: ______________________________________\nDate: __________________________________________\n\nCompliance Review\nName: __________________________________________\nSignature: ______________________________________\nDate: __________________________________________\n\nCompany Stamp\n[Stamp Here]', now(), now()),

('16_client_data_consent_privacy_acknowledgment', 'Client Data Consent & Privacy Acknowledgment', 'NDA', 'v1.0', 'Published', E'Client Data Consent & Privacy Acknowledgment\n\nPurpose\nThis document records the Client''s consent and acknowledgment regarding the collection, use, and processing of personal data by MiCasa Real Estate LLC in compliance with UAE PDPL (Federal Decree-Law No. 45 of 2021).\n\n1. Data Controller\nMiCasa Real Estate LLC is the data controller for the personal data collected in connection with real estate brokerage services.\n\n2. Personal Data Collected\nThe data may include identity documents, contact details, financial information, property preferences, transaction records, and communications necessary for brokerage services and regulatory compliance.\n\n3. Purposes of Processing\nPersonal data is processed for the following purposes:\n(a) Client onboarding, verification, and KYC/AML compliance.\n(b) Property search, marketing, and transaction facilitation.\n(c) Contracting, invoicing, and regulatory reporting.\n(d) Customer service, dispute handling, and audit compliance.\n\n4. Legal Basis\nProcessing is based on the Client''s consent, performance of a contract, and compliance with legal obligations under UAE law.\n\n5. Data Sharing and Transfers\nMiCasa may share data with relevant authorities, service providers, and counterparties as required for the transaction, subject to confidentiality and lawful processing requirements. Cross-border transfers, if required, will be conducted in accordance with PDPL requirements and safeguards.\n\n6. Data Retention\nPersonal data will be retained for the period required by applicable law and for legitimate business purposes, including audit and dispute resolution.\n\n7. Client Rights\nThe Client has the right to access, correct, request deletion (where applicable), restrict processing, and withdraw consent subject to legal and contractual obligations.\n\n8. Contact\nFor data protection inquiries, contact: ____________________________\nEmail: _________________________________________________\nPhone: _________________________________________________\n\n9. Governing Law\nThis acknowledgment is governed by the laws of the United Arab Emirates and applicable regulations in the Emirate of Abu Dhabi.\n\nSignatures\n\nClient\nName: __________________________________________\nSignature: ______________________________________\nDate: __________________________________________\n\nBroker Representative (MiCasa Real Estate LLC)\nName: __________________________________________\nSignature: ______________________________________\nDate: __________________________________________\n\nCompany Stamp\n[Stamp Here]', now(), now()),

('17_complaint_dispute_incident_register', 'Complaint, Dispute & Incident Register', 'Other', 'v1.0', 'Published', E'Complaint, Dispute & Incident Register\n\nPurpose\nThis register records complaints, disputes, and operational incidents for regulatory compliance, internal escalation, and resolution tracking.\n\n1. Register Details\nRegister Period: _________________________________________\nPrepared By: ____________________________________________\n\n2. Case Log\nCase No. | Date Received | Complainant / Party | Type | Summary | Status | Resolution Date\n--- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | ---\n________ | ____________ | ___________________ | _____ | ______________________ | ______ | ____________\n________ | ____________ | ___________________ | _____ | ______________________ | ______ | ____________\n________ | ____________ | ___________________ | _____ | ______________________ | ______ | ____________\n\n3. Escalation and Actions\nFor each case, the following information must be recorded in the case file:\n(a) Evidence collected and communications log.\n(b) Internal review and decision notes.\n(c) Any authority notifications and response dates.\n\n4. Governing Law\nThis register is maintained in accordance with the laws of the United Arab Emirates and applicable regulations in the Emirate of Abu Dhabi.\n\nSignatures\n\nCompliance Officer\nName: __________________________________________\nSignature: ______________________________________\nDate: __________________________________________\n\nOperations Manager\nName: __________________________________________\nSignature: ______________________________________\nDate: __________________________________________\n\nCompany Stamp\n[Stamp Here]', now(), now()),

('18_internal_agent_governance_pack', 'Internal Agent Governance Pack', 'Other', 'v1.0', 'Published', E'Internal Agent Governance Pack\n\nPurpose\nThis internal governance pack sets out MiCasa Real Estate LLC policies for commission, clawbacks, conduct, and conflict of interest declarations for agents and brokers.\n\n1. Commission Policy\nMiCasa pays commission to agents based on executed transactions and verified receipts of commission from clients. Commission eligibility requires:\n(a) A signed brokerage authorization or representation agreement.\n(b) Documented role in the transaction recorded in the CRM.\n(c) Compliance with AML/KYC and regulatory requirements.\nPayment schedules are subject to finance approval and may be adjusted for applicable deductions or VAT requirements.\n\n2. Clawback Policy\nMiCasa reserves the right to claw back commissions where:\n(a) A transaction is canceled or reversed after payment.\n(b) Commission was paid based on inaccurate or incomplete information.\n(c) Regulatory non-compliance or misconduct is confirmed.\nThe agent will be notified in writing and provided a summary of the basis for any clawback.\n\n3. Code of Conduct\nAgents shall:\n(a) Act honestly and in the best interests of clients.\n(b) Comply with Abu Dhabi DMT/ADM regulations and UAE law.\n(c) Avoid misrepresentation and disclose material facts.\n(d) Maintain client confidentiality and data privacy.\n(e) Avoid conflicts of interest and disclose them immediately.\n(f) Use company systems and branding in accordance with policies.\n\n4. Conflict of Interest Declaration\nThe Agent declares the following:\n(a) I have disclosed any personal or financial interest in properties, clients, or counterparties related to my work.\n(b) I will notify MiCasa immediately of any potential conflicts that arise.\n(c) I understand that undisclosed conflicts may lead to disciplinary action.\n\nDeclared Conflicts (if any):\n__________________________________________________________________\n__________________________________________________________________\n\n5. Acknowledgment\nI acknowledge that I have read, understood, and will comply with this Governance Pack. I understand that failure to comply may result in disciplinary action or termination.\n\n6. Governing Law\nThis governance pack is maintained in accordance with the laws of the United Arab Emirates and applicable regulations in the Emirate of Abu Dhabi.\n\nSignatures\n\nAgent\nName: __________________________________________\nSignature: ______________________________________\nDate: __________________________________________\n\nCompliance Officer\nName: __________________________________________\nSignature: ______________________________________\nDate: __________________________________________\n\nCompany Stamp\n[Stamp Here]', now(), now());